[2026-03-09T01:15:49Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013QufeHuwuuy6MmqQtP7ymz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have found all the information you requested. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n## cmdHealth Function Implementation\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/health.go` (lines 24-67)\n\nThe `cmdHealth` function is a CLI command that displays project health summaries by making HTTP requests to the daemon. Here's what it does:\n\n1. **Reads environment variable** `CLOCHE_HTTP` to determine the daemon's HTTP address\n2. **Makes HTTP GET request** to `/api/projects` endpoint\n3. **Parses JSON response** containing project health data\n4. **Displays results** in a formatted table with columns: PROJECT, STATUS, PASSED, FAILED, TOTAL\n5. **Color-codes status** output for TTY terminals (green, yellow, red)\n\nThe function also includes two helper functions:\n- `colorStatus()` (lines 69-83) - Applies ANSI color codes based on health status\n- `isTTY()` (lines 85-91) - Detects if output is going to a terminal\n\n**Data structures:**\n- `healthData` - Contains status, passed, failed, total counts\n- `projectHealth` - Contains dir, label, and health data for each project\n\n## Go Files in cmd/cloche/\n\nThe following Go source files exist in `/workspace/cmd/cloche/`:\n\n1. `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - Main CLI entry point with command routing\n2. `/workspace/cmd/cloche/health.go` - Health command implementation\n3. `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` - Project initialization\n4. `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go` - Poll command for waiting on runs\n5. `/workspace/cmd/cloche/orchestrate_test.go` - Tests for orchestrate command\n6. `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init_test.go` - Tests for init command\n7. `/workspace/cmd/cloche/health_test.go` - Tests for health command\n\n## Makefile Build Targets\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/Makefile`\n\n**Key build targets:**\n\n- `build` - Compiles all three binaries: cloche, cloched, cloche-agent\n- `test` - Runs all tests with verbose output\n- `test-short` - Runs tests with short flag\n- `lint` - Runs `go vet` on the codebase\n- `proto` - Generates gRPC code from protobuf definitions\n- `docker-base` - Builds base Docker image for agents\n- `docker-build` - Builds agent container image\n- `install` - Builds everything, stops existing daemon, installs binaries to $(PREFIX)/bin (default: ~/.local), and restarts daemon\n- `clean` - Removes the bin/ directory\n\nThe cmdHealth command is invoked early in the main() function (line 33-35) before establishing a gRPC connection to the daemon, since it communicates via HTTP instead."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af909c5556cb71c48 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 22295\ntool_uses: 6\nduration_ms: 11934</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5170bdb-c8b4-480e-a334-260ee3446a61","uuid":"76356901-6cca-49f3-9123-de0230a071c7","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find the cmdHealth function implementation - search for \"func cmdHealth\" or \"cmdHealth\" in the cmd/cloche/ directory. Also check for any other Go files in cmd/cloche/. Also check the Makefile for build targets.","agentId":"af909c5556cb71c48","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have found all the information you requested. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n## cmdHealth Function Implementation\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/health.go` (lines 24-67)\n\nThe `cmdHealth` function is a CLI command that displays project health summaries by making HTTP requests to the daemon. Here's what it does:\n\n1. **Reads environment variable** `CLOCHE_HTTP` to determine the daemon's HTTP address\n2. **Makes HTTP GET request** to `/api/projects` endpoint\n3. **Parses JSON response** containing project health data\n4. **Displays results** in a formatted table with columns: PROJECT, STATUS, PASSED, FAILED, TOTAL\n5. **Color-codes status** output for TT